article.headline: Dayton 30, Morehead St. 28
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. -- Dayton used a dominant ground game and solid special teams play to beat Morehead State 30-28 on Saturday. The Flyers (5-3, 3-2 Pioneer Football League) rushed for 317 yards and kept possession for 34:43, nearly 10 minutes longer than Morehead State, which has lost three in a row. Dayton scored its most points in a game this season, and got three field goals from Nate Miller and a 32-yard punt return for a score by Tyler Hujik. Taylor Harris rushed for 216 yards for the Flyers. Morehead State (2-6, 1-4) led 7-0 before Dayton scored 20 unanswered points. The Flyers led 30-21 after Will Bardo threw his second touchdown pass of the game, a 26-yarder to Branden Johnson, with 2:25 remaining. Zach Lewis, who threw for 304 yards and three touchdowns for the Eagles, passed to Dante Sawyer for a 2-yard score for the final margin with 1:07 remaining. .
